 					<entry>command line</entry>
 					<entry>EC2</entry>
 				</row>
 				<row>
 					<entry>S3 ACL</entry>
 					<entry>&#160;</entry>
 					<entry>X</entry>
 					<entry>&#160;</entry>
 					<entry>X</entry>
 					<entry>XML ACL</entry>
 					<entry>S3</entry>
 				</row>
 				<row>
 					<entry>S3 Bucket Policy</entry>
 					<entry>&#160;</entry>
 					<entry>X</entry>
 					<entry>X</entry>
 					<entry>X</entry>
 					<entry>JSON</entry>
 					<entry>S3</entry>
 				</row>
 			</tbody>
 		</tgroup>
 	</table>
 	<p>Eucalyptus uses a general permission policy language that is extended from the IAM policy language. This policy language is written in JSON and specifies resource access permissions at all levels, while still maintaining compatibility with Amazon AWS permissions.</p> 
 	<p>This policy language allows you to specify permissions for users and groups, both within and across accounts, to access Eucalyptus resources. The Eucalyptus permissions are attached to principals only.</p>
 	
